// Bhaal's Fire
@201    = ~Bhaal's Fire: +3 Flaming Longsword

The origins of this longsword are so thoroughly shrouded in mystery that none know who forged it or even where it was forged.  Some have speculated that Bhaal himself may have created this sword himself.  However, the more immediate history of this weapon is reasonably well known.  Bhaal's Fire seems to have remained in Icewind Dale for about two centuries, always seeming to be a part of any conflict that arose in that time.

STATISTICS:

Damage:  1d8 + 3
Attack Bonus:  +3
Enchantment:  +3
Damage Type:  Slashing
Special: 
    15% chance target is Stunned
    Flame: +1d6 fire damage
Weight: 4 lb.
Feat Requirement:  Martial Weapon, Large Sword
Type:  One-handed~


