@258    = ~Frostguard~ 
@259    = ~Frostguard: +2 Studded Leather Armor

Legend tells of a mysterious human ranger who patrolled Icewind Dale, protecting townsfolk and barbarian alike.  Although welcomed by both, Rolf Haaken was rarely seen in any barbarian village and almost never set foot in any of the Ten-Towns. None ever knew where Haaken actually lived, if such a place even existed.  All that was ever certain was, for a time, if danger threatened any traveller in the Dale, Haaken was probably not far behind, ready to aid those in need.

Haaken's armor, Frostguard, is rather non-descript set of studded leathers that is ashen gray in color and appears well-worn.  But despite its worn appearance, any ranger or druid who is able to don Frostguard will never doubt its protective qualities, for they will instantly feel the blessing of Mielikki's warm embrace.

STATISTICS:

Armor Bonus: +5
Max Dex Bonus:  +5
Armor Check Penalty:  0
Arcane Spell Failure:  15%
Special:
    5/- Cold Resistance
    Wearer is under the effect of the spell Protection from Evil
Weight: 15 lb.~


