@343    = ~Skirmisher~
@344    = ~Skirmisher: +4 Composite Shortbow

Atheria Tarathel, an elven ranger and devout worshiper of Mielikki, spent many years defending the great forests of the Dalelands, ranging from Hillsfar in the north to Tilverton to the south.  Atheria's preference for the shortbow over the longbow was more a matter of her short stature, than any inability to pull a strong bow.  Indeed, Atheria prefered the strong pull of a powerful composite shortbow over a weaker non-composite bow.

Many were the days that Atheria and Skirmisher fought many times times her number in the deepwood and the dales.  Atheria would take a few shots,  slay two or three foes, and then use her great speed to withdraw before any of her enemies could reach her, only to begin the stalking process once again.

Unfortunately, a day came when a group of Malarites, angered by Atheria's ardent defense of the forests and the great numbers of their hunters and priests she'd slain, arranged a rather large ambush for her.  What this force was composed of, none know.  All that is known is that Atheria Tarathel managed to slay all but a few of her ambushers before she fell herself, unable to escape from the overwhelming numbers.  Skirmisher itself was presumed to have been lost forever, as it had not been seen since.  Some believe that Mielikki herself may have snatched up Skirmisher after Atheria fell, rather than allow it to fall into Malarite hands.

STATISTICS:

Damage: +6 (missile)
Attack Bonus: +4
Special:
  Increased movement rate
Weight: 2 lb.
Feat Requirement:  Martial Weapon, Bow
Type:  Two-handed
Requires STR 14 to use~


