@421    = ~Hoarfrost~
@422    = ~Hoarfrost: +3 Katana

The history of this weapon is both long and very vague.  It was not made in Faerun, but in the distant land of Kara-Tur.  None know the true name of its last owner.  She is said to have only gone by name of Raven during her time travelling Faerun.  It is believed that Raven was some sort of Kara-Turan knight, called a "samurai" by most accounts, who was forced to flee her family's ancestral lands.  Most tales say that Raven fled rather than fight to prevent her enemy, apparantly some thoroughly dishonorable overlord, from gaining her family's most prized possession, Hoarfrost.  

When Raven arrived in Faerun, she offered her services to any chivilric order that would accept her blade.  In that time, she acted in nearly every way as a paladin without any divine patron or powers.  Raven built up an outstanding reputation as a great warrior and trustworthy companion and was gladly accepted as an ally of nearly all chivilric orders across Faerun.  However, while in Calimport, Raven disappeared without a trace, never to be seen again.  Some wondered if she was a victim of an assassination at the hands of some group whom she'd defeated.  Others wondered if she merely decided to settle down and end her adventuring days.

Raven's sword, Hoarfrost, is her family's honor sword and has been enchanted with the spirits of many of her ancestors who were also honored samurai.  With Hoarfrost in her hands, it was said that Raven never knew true defeat nor dishonor during her days in Faerun, at least until she disappeared.

Hoarfrost is a Kara-turan bastard sword, called a "katana".  While capable of being used by a truly skilled Kara-turan warrior one-handed, many prefer to use it two handed, taking advantage of its long handle to provide greater balance and power in combat.  However, for some reason, perhaps the spirits of the sword, anyone wielding Hoarfrost cannot help but wield it two-handed.  Furthermore, it is said that the spirits of the sword only speak with the raging power of winter from which Hoarfrost takes its name whenever the blade strikes.

STATISTICS:

Damage:  1d10 + 3
Attack Bonus:  +3
Enchantment:   +3
Damage Type:  Slashing
Special:
    Keen: Increases chance of scoring a critical hit
    Frost: +2d6 cold damage
    Numbing Cold: 10% chance target is slowed for 3 rounds (Will save to resist)
Weight:  5 lb.
Feat Requirement:  Exotic Weapon, Bastard Sword
Type:  One-handed~


