@900    = ~Arpathia~
@901    = ~Arpathia: +2 Composite Shortbow

This magnificent composite shortbow has a history that is both heroic and yet mysterious.  Many are the tales of the strange human barbarian, Karthag, and his bow, named Arpathia, apparantly after the land from whence he came.  However, none know of such a land and it has long been assumed by the most learned masters of lore that Karthag may have come from some other dimension, although there is no way to prove this assumption.

Not the largest or strongest of warrior, Karthag was most at home on the back of a horse with Arpathia in hand.  When fighting with his magnificent bow Arpathia, Karthag was incredibly difficult to strike in battle, whether with weapons or magic.

What is clear to the skilled eyes of archer and bowyer alike is that Arpathia is a magnificently constructed composite shortbow.  Lesser eyes may look at this rugged shortbow and think that it cannot match the power and elegance of a good longbow.And while it is true that it does not match the beauty of many finely-crafted elven longbows, Arpathia's true beauty is in its performance.  In the hands of a strong-armed, skilled archer, Arpathia is as fine a horsebow as can be imagined.

STATISTICS:

Damage: +4 (missile)
Attack Bonus: +2
Special:
  Saving Throw Bonus: +2 to Reflex saves
  Armor Bonus: +2 (generic)
Weight: 2 lb.
Feat Requirement:  Martial Weapon, Bow
Type:  Two-handed
Minimum Strength of 14 required~


