@912    = ~Magar's Axe~
@913    = ~Magar's Axe: +1 Massive Greataxe

This massive two-handed woodsman's axe once belonged to verbeeg named Magar.  Magar was actually a rather decent sort, as verbeegs go.  For many years, he worked with a number of human and dwarven woodsmen, calling most of them friend until one day when they were ambushed by a large group of angry treants.  All of Magar's friends were slain before he could stop the treants.  Angered byond endurance, Magar cut down every last treant with his mighty axe. After the battle, Magar, inconsolable over the loss of his friends, swore that he would chop down every last tree in the forest in the vain hope of slaying every treant he could find. 

However, Magar was never able to fulfill his oath.  Having heard of the verbeeg's attempt to destroy the forest, a group of shadow druids sought out Magar to defend the forest from his vengeance.  Although the shadow druids were able to surprise Magar, his trusty axe prevented the druids from entangling him as Magar charged into their ranks.  While Magar slew at least a half dozen of the druids, their numbers were simply too great for even the mighty Magar to overcome.

For many years, Magar's Axe was presumed lost to the woods, or perhaps hidden by the shadow druids, until it turned up in Neverwinter.

STATISTICS:

