Stormspear is an exceptionally well manufactured weapon. The spearhead is crafted of the finest steel with a mithril edge.  The shaft is solid oak with a some steel bands.  Along the shaft are a series of glowing dwarven runes cast in silver.  The weapon is light, fast, and deadly.

Stormspear can call upon the elemental power of lightning.  With every successful hit, Stormspear shocks its target with a charge of electricity.  And once per day it can shoot a powerful bolt of lightning.  Stormspear was crafted by the dwarven smith Braegar of Dorn's Deep.

STATISTICS:

Damage:  1d8 + 2
Attack Bonus:  +2
Enchantment:  +2
Damage Type:  Piercing
Special:
  Shock: +1d6 electric damage
  Spell Power: Can cast the spell Lightning Bolt once per day
Weight: 5 lb.
Feat Requirement:  Martial Weapon, Polearm
Type:  Two-handed~


@938    = ~Stormspike~
@939    = ~Stormspike: +3 Spear

Stormspike is an exceptionally well manufactured weapon. The spearhead is crafted of the finest steel with a mithril edge.  The shaft is solid oak with a some steel bands.  Along the shaft are a series of glowing dwarven runes cast in silver.  The weapon is light, fast, and deadly.

Stormspike can call upon the elemental power of lightning.  With every successful hit, Stormspike shocks its target with a charge of electricity.  And twice per day it can shoot a powerful bolt of lightning.  And once per day, Stormspike can call forth an even more powerful chain of lightning bolts.  Stormspike was crafted by the dwarven smith Braegar of Dorn's Deep.

STATISTICS:

Damage:  1d8 + 3
