Enchantment:  +3
Damage Type:  Piercing
Special:
  Shocking Burst: +1d6 electrical damage and 10% chance of +2d10 extra
  Spell Power: Can cast the spell Lightning Bolt twice per day
  Spell Power: Can cast the spell Chain Lightning once per day
Weight: 5 lb.
Feat Requirement:  Martial Weapon, Polearm
Type:  Two-handed~


@940    = ~Raging Spirits~
@941    = ~Raging Spirits: +2 Greatsword

Rulfgar, grandfather of the great barbarian king Wylfdene, was a renowned warrior within his clan.  But Rulfgar was almost as equally well known for his unmatched temper and his ability to focus his rage in battle.  However, one day while fighting a massive cave bear, Rulfgar was gravely wounded.  But rather than give in to his wounds, Rulfgar asked the clan shamans to embed the power of his rage into his greatsword, so that his descendents could tap into his warrior's spirit to aid them in battle.

STATISTICS:

Damage:  2d6 + 2
Attack Bonus:  +2
Enchantment:  +2
Damage Type:  Slashing
Special:
    Spell Power: Can cast the spell Emotion Rage (on self only) 2/day.
Weight: 12 lb.
Feat Requirement:  Martial Weapon, Great Sword
Type:  Two-handed~




