@962    = ~Ring of the Vampire Hunter~
@963    = ~Vampires have long been among the most feared of undead creatures, for they have far greater intelligence than the average undead creature.  And for almost as long, these vile creatures of the night have been hunted by those with the strength, skill, and courage to combat their evil.  This particular ring belonged to the leader of one such group of vampire hunters whose name has been lost to the mists of time.  It is said that this warrior, a woman of unmatched skill and strength, was so feared by vampires that eventually none would knowingly face her in battle.  How this ring came to be here is totally unknown.

STATISTICS:

User is under the effects of the spell Negative Plane Protection while equipped.
Weight: 0 lb.~


// Gauntlets of Elven Might
@964    = ~These slender steel gauntlets were crafted by the elven smith Idrial Ashleaf and enchanted by his brother, Beldan.  The pair gave the gauntlets to their cousin, Galain, when he alone returned from a failed quest to destroy a venerable green dragon in the forests of what are now known as Amn.  The three elves made a pact to avenge their kin in ten years time.  The subsequent adventures of the trio were immortalized in Merador of Waterdeep's epic "Three Avengers" ballads.  The songs, sixteen in number, tell all of the adventures that the group went on.  From the Ballad of the Goblin King to the Ballad of Green Night, every deed is retold.  Unfortunately, the history of Galain's gauntlets end with the final bars of Green Night.  The rest is shrouded in mystery.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class Bonus: +1 (generic)
Saving Throw Bonus: +1 to all Saves
Strength:  +2
Only Usable By:
 Fighters, Barbarians, Rangers, Paladins~


